criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Moderate or severe ARDS, defined according to the Berlin definition (2);

          -  Endotracheal intubation or tracheostomy

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Severe heart failure/cardiogenic shock;

          -  Pulmonary arterial hypertension requiring systemic vasodilators;

          -  Contraindications to esophageal balloon: esophageal pathology (stricture, perforation,
             high grade of varices), recent history of esophageal or gastric surgery, upper GI
             tract bleeding, severe coagulopathy and nasal trauma;

          -  Contraindications to Electrical Impedance Tomography (EIT): a temporary or permanent
             pacemaker, or implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD);

          -  Age < 16 years.
